msgctxt "talk07"
msgid ""
"<1.so>The <2.se_co>Torin Wetland<3.re_co> lies to the west of\n"
"here.<4.pa> You're aware that there are\n"
"<5.se_co>Guardians <6.re_co>there? Not just one, either...\n"
"<7.so><8.te_si><9.se_co>Two <10.re_co>of them!!<11.te_si>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<12.so>You know how dangerous they are...<13.pa>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<14.so>So, sonny boy... <15.pa>I'd like you to find and\n"
"wallop <16.se_co>both <17.re_co>of them in <18.se_co>Torin "
"Wetland<19.re_co>.\n"
"Then come and see me."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk09"
msgid "<1.so>Hand!<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: sound
#. 3: text_size
msgctxt "talk10"
msgid "<1.te_si><2.so>Didn't I tell you...<3.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: set_colour (grey)
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: sound
#. 4: text_size
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: sound
#. 7: pause (short)
#. 8: sound
#. 9: pause (short)
#. 10: sound
#. 11: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk11"
msgid ""
"<1.se_co><2.te_si><3.so>I suppose I must endure engaging with the\n"
"common folk if I hope to get something done...<4.te_si><5.re_co>\n"
"\n"
"<6.so>You've no doubt heard of the ferocious\n"
"Hagie? That's me. But I...<7.pa>got everything\n"
"I wanted.\n"
"<8.so>Lately my days have felt so empty.<9.pa>\n"
"The only things that thrill me now are\n"
"true risks to life and limb.\n"
"<10.so>Everything else just feels...<11.pa>hollow."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk12"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'm sorry? You don't want the <2.se_co>100\n"
"rupees<3.re_co>?<4.pa> All right, then."
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: sound
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: text_size
msgctxt "talk13"
msgid "<1.te_si><2.so>Hmm... <3.pa>And you are...<4.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk15"
msgid "<1.so>Do you need something else from me?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk16"
msgid "<1.so>It's you..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: sound
#. 4: set_colour (grey)
#. 5: text_size
#. 6: text_size
#. 7: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk17"
msgid ""
"<1.so>...If you think you can put one over on\n"
"me, I have grave news for you, sonny.<2.pa>\n"
"\n"
"<3.so><4.se_co><5.te_si>Just the sort of shoddy, corner-cutting job I "
"expect\n"
"from the common rabble...<6.te_si><7.re_co>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk19"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If you're clear on the deal, then go take\n"
"out the <2.se_co>two Guardians<3.re_co> walking around\n"
"<4.se_co>Torin Wetland<5.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk20"
msgid ""
"<1.so>OK. OK. I saw the whole thing.<2.pa>\n"
"You did splendidly. I'll give you the\n"
"rest of the reward, as I promised."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: sound
#. 4: sound
#. 5: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk21"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Why do you look so disappointed?\n"
"It can't be because the reward is lower\n"
"than the down payment, can it?\n"
"<2.so>You commoners with your notions and\n"
"assumptions...\n"
"\n"
"<3.so>The whole idea that a down payment is a\n"
"small part of the final payment is an idea\n"
"entirely unique to the common folk!\n"
"<4.so>In any case, our business is concluded.<5.pa>\n"
"Go over there. Or anywhere, really.\n"
"Anywhere that isn't. Right. Here."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: sound
#. 4: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk22"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I...<2.pa>got everything I wanted.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<3.so>But I'll tell you, there are some things\n"
"out there... <4.pa>Things that all the money in\n"
"the world can't get you..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: text_size
msgctxt "talk23"
msgid "<1.so><2.te_si>Haaah... <3.pa>I've grown weak...<4.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: text_size
#. 2: sound
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: text_size
#. 5: pause (longer)
#. 6: text_size
#. 7: text_size
msgctxt "talk24"
msgid ""
"<1.te_si><2.so>My daughter's health has improved<3.pa>...\n"
"Does that mean that we don't need this house\n"
"anymore?<4.te_si><5.pa><6.te_si> Hmmm...<7.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk26"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'm going sunbathing with my family.<2.pa>\n"
"You're in my wayâ€”cease to be so."
msgstr ""

